    "gitCommitHash": "72dc1932456ad2aa30ad7be30f0cff835d2e8dce",
    "gitCommitMessage": "Fix Guideline 2.1(a): resolve launch crash on iPad (iOS 26)\n\nRoot cause: i18n was initialised inside an async .then() callback,\nso useTranslation() accessed an unset React context on the very first\nrender on fast devices (iPad Air M3). The ErrorBoundary caught the\nresulting TypeError and displayed \"Something went wrong\" on launch.\n\nFix: call i18n.use(initReactI18next).init() synchronously with a safe\nEnglish default so t() always works on first render. The async callback\nnow only calls i18n.changeLanguage() once the saved preference loads.\n\nAlso:\n- Remove dead debugging code in sign-in.tsx (useWindowDimensions?.toString?.())\n- Add structured error logging in ErrorBoundary.tsx for future diagnostics\n- Bump iOS buildNumber to 17 for new submission\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
